I had to stop by the grocery store to pick up some steaks. I've done so well since getting off of work today. I had a salad. I had chocolate covered almonds, but I didn't go overboard. I didn't touch the popcorn in the kitchen cabinet. When I saw it, I kept looking back to it. The cabinet door was left open. I kept looking at it from the living room. I can taste it even now. But I closed the cabinet.

When I stopped by the grocery store, I bought pads. But I walked through a few aisles. I saw the lunchables. I saw cookies and crackers and chips and donuts. I saw the frozen food aisle-- the one with pizza. I stopped myself from walking further. I just turned down the closest aisle, the cookie aisle, and walked to the register.

Old habits die fucking hard.

But today, I am the winner.

Today would be day one, but I guess I'm going to have to resist my current craving and start over right now. I had some chocolate covered almonds and the taste of chocolate melted on my molars. It was delicious. Then I took two huge, hurried handfuls of white cheddar popcorn. The popcorn gave me a rush. I immediately wanted to eat the whole bag. I put it up. Ugh.

Then I made two eggs with no cheese. I'm still hungry. I have a cup of coffee to drink. This is my life now.

My problem in a nutshell-- the addicts dilemma: I can't stop once I've started. And I can't stop from starting again PART ONE- foods Any food that I can't stop eating once I start is a food that causes cravings. Those are the foods I need to eliminate. Plain chocolate, candy bars, cheese, french fries, bread, bagels, rice, gummy bears, mike & ikes, ice cream, donuts, fruit snacks, frozen meals, pizza, pizza rolls, ranch dressing, What is in common between these foods? Sugar, the carb foods (bread, bagels, rice) are types of sugars. but the other ones are candies. Sugar. and Cheese. I know cheese is a problem because I eat it straight out of the bag, in hurried handfuls with my face in the fridge. Sugar, cheese. chocolate PART TWO- behaviors secret eating (secret snacks) eating in my car going out to pick up something then destroying the evidence fast food vending machines eating to feel FULL. to feel stuffed. eating to the point of discomfort, every single time. don't eat between meals don't eat pre-prepared meals. don't eat fast foods, vending machine plastic wrapped foods. eat the meals that are planned and that take time to prepare.

Apparently, livejournal is still a thing. I wish I could print out all my old entries. This is interesting. I used to write, and have dreams and be really idealistic and super descriptive. I miss it, sort of, but I think I have reached the point in my life where I no longer believe in it all anymore. I guess my worldview is tainted by age. Was this supposed to happen so early? I figured it would take til my 30s at least.

You have GOT to be fucking kidding me!

I had a friend repair some stuff on my car for me
he charged me 500 bucks
which is fair b/c at a real shop it would have been 800, or probably more than a 1000 bucks.

I also bought two new tires, for a total of 140 bucks. 

That's a total of 640 bucks I have spent on my car this week.

Then today, I went to the shop b/c I need an alignment (did you know a simple fucking alignment costs 70 fucking bucks! I couldn't believe it!).

But on top of that, they can't do an alignment until I get my rear shocks replaced... And when I get the shocks I also gotta get the springs. Those two things would be about 300 bucks, but then the shop wants to add a labor fee of TWO HUNDRED AND THIRTY DOLLARS. 

So, on top of the 640 bucks I just put into this car, they wanna charge me an additional 630 dollars to do the rest. 


That puts me nearly 1300 dollars in the hole here. 





And the kicker?
I only paid 800 bucks for my car to begin with!



:( I am feeling money sad right now. I can't handle it.

Two class periods late already and I still haven't found a way to start writing this paper. Why do I put it off? Why do I read articles on Obama's tax returns and scroll through my itunes instead? I means, it's not like the pressure isn't on... I must be off. Just, just, just. A minimizer.

My friend Vince Binder (pronounced: bin-der, kinda like been-der but definitely not bind-er) has been missing since April 2nd. 3 fugitives that escaped from a LA jail have been linked via some sort of unmentionable physical evidence as well as a offhand comment under interrogation. I keep looking at the websites and articles to find out more. I read and re-read articles trying to understand a different word. I have not cried and for that I actually feel guilty.

I broke down in my professors office and she offered me extra time on the paper, but I still haven't got it done. Dinner in 2 hours. Alcohol after that. I have all my quotes typed up and now organized into concepts. I have made sketchy outlines. Speaking with her limited my topic, so I feel OK. I don't know why I can't start, won't start it. Everyone else already has this god forsaken paper off their plates. Why is my still sitting here, molding and polluting my air-brain waves?

I watched the film version of "the hours" by michael cunningham. many differences. need to do an analysis of the significance of one scene. filmic importance, textual significance. due tuesday, tomorrow. need to write a paper on mrs. dalloway. I feel weird because i always like to write papers about madness and identity. someone tell me what to do.

"What I fear most, I think, is the death of the imagination. When the sky outside is merely pink, and the rooftops merely black: that photographic mind which paradoxically tells the truth, but the worthless truth, about the world. it is that synthesizing spirit, that shaping force, which prolifically sprouts and makes up its own worlds with more inventiveness than God which I desire. If I sit still and don't do anything, the world goes on beating like a slack drum, without meaning. We must be moving, working, making dreams to run toward; the poeverty of life without dreams is too horrible to imagine: it is that kind of madness which is worst: the kind with fancies and hallucinations would be a bosch-ish relief. I listen always for footsteps coming up the stairs and hate them if they are not for me. Why, why, can I not be an ascetic for a while, instead of always teetering on the edge of wanting complete solitude for work and reading, and, so much, so much, the gestures of hands and words of other human beings. Well, after this Racine paper, this Ronsard-purgatory, this Sophocles, I shall write: letters and prose and poetry, toward the end of the week; I must be stoic till then."
-Sylvia Plath, Feb 25, 1956

Euphoric, energetic, talkative, and mentally allert.
These are the immediate symptoms of crack or cocaine.
These are also symptoms of a policy debater.
Euphoric- we learn a lot and get cocky and think we are going to do great.
Energetic- 5 fucking scenarios of extinction baby.
Talkative- how many words/coherent arguments can you say in 5 minutes?
Mentally allert- When you do the intellectual activity that we do at the level at which we do it, it gets you mentally allert.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Short-Term Symptoms of Cocaine Use:
Increased energy
Decreased appetite
Mental alertness
Increased heart rate
Increased blood pressure
Constricted blood vessels
Increased temperature
Dilated pupils

Short-Term Symptoms of Debate:
Increased energy
Decreased appetite
Mental alertness
Increased heart rate
Increased blood pressure
Constricted blood vessels
Increased temperature
Dilated pupils
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
The duration of cocaine's immediate euphoric effects depends upon the route of administration. The faster the absorption, the more intense the high. Also, the faster the absorption, the shorter the duration of action. The high from snorting is relatively slow in onset, and may last 15 to 30 minutes, while that from smoking may last 5 to 10 minutes

The duration of debate's immediate euphoric effects depends upon the route of administration. The faster the absorption, the more intense the high. Also, the faster the absorption, the shorter the duration of action. The high from snorting is relatively slow in onset, and may last 15 to 30 minutes, while that from smoking may last 5 to 10 minutes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Cocaine is a powerfully addictive drug. Once having tried cocaine, an individual may have difficulty predicting or controlling the extent to which he or she will continue to use the drug. Cocaine's stimulant and addictive effects are thought to be primarily a result of its ability to inhibit the reabsorption of dopamine by nerve cells. Dopamine is released as part of the brain's reward system, and is either directly or indirectly involved in the addictive properties of every major drug of abuse.

Debate is a powerfully addictive game. Once having tried debate, an individual may have difficulty predicting or controlling the extent to which he or she will continue to debate. Debate's stimulant and addictive effects are thought to be primarily a result of its ability to inhibit the reabsorption of intellectual masterbation by nerve cells. Intellectual masterbation is released as part of the brain's reward system, and is either directly or indirectly involved in the addictive properties of policy debate.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Long-Term Symptoms of Cocaine Addiction
Irritability
Mood disturbances
Restlessness
Paranoia
Auditory hallucinations

Long-Term Symptoms of Debate Addiction
Irritability
Mood disturbances
Restlessness
Paranoia
Auditory hallucinations
